nascent: Data quality processes are not defined.
emerging: Data quality and standards are loosely defined.
expanding: Data quality has been defined with minimum standards.
optimising: Improvements to our existing data quality process are in-progress.
mature: Data quality processes have been refined based on review.

nascent: We do not have trusted data architecture protected with strong data governance to manage our data.
emerging: We are in the process of defining and developing data architecture and governance standards.
expanding: A defined and trusted data architecture protected with strong data governance is increasingly utilised.
optimising: Data is consistently managed in a defined data architecture protected with strong data governance.
mature: There are routine review and improvement processes of our data architecture and governance standards.
